    <body class="- topic/body " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/server_side_building_and_publishing.dita" xtrc="body:1;11:11">
        <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/server_side_building_and_publishing.dita" xtrc="p:1;12:12">The <xref href="https://www.oxygenxml.com/publishing_engine.html" format="html" scope="external" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/server_side_building_and_publishing.dita" xtrc="xref:1;13:34"><?ditaot usertext?>Oxygen Publishing Engine</xref> is a commercial licensed
            command-line tool based on the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/server_side_building_and_publishing.dita" xtrc="uicontrol:1;14:55">DITA Open Toolkit</uicontrol>. This means that
            instead of publishing directly from <ph keyref="oxygen" class="- topic/ph " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/server_side_building_and_publishing.dita" xtrc="ph:1;15:70">Oxygen XML Editor</ph>, you can use an integration
            server to run the transformations and publish the output or simply use it from a
            command-line interface. </p>
        <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/server_side_building_and_publishing.dita" xtrc="p:2;18:12">Possible ways to run the Oxygen Publishing Engine on the server side:<ul id="ul_bhp_gyf_vzb" class="- topic/ul " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/server_side_building_and_publishing.dita" xtrc="ul:1;19:37">
                <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/server_side_building_and_publishing.dita" xtrc="li:1;20:21"><xref href="building_and_publishing_using_script.dita" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/server_side_building_and_publishing.dita" xtrc="xref:2;20:77" type="concept"><?ditaot gentext?>Building and Publishing Using a Script</xref>.</li>
                <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/server_side_building_and_publishing.dita" xtrc="li:2;21:21"><xref href="building_validating_and_publishing_using_github_actions.dita" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/server_side_building_and_publishing.dita" xtrc="xref:3;22:23" type="concept"><?ditaot gentext?>Building, Validating, and Publishing Using GitHub Actions</xref>.</li>
                <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/server_side_building_and_publishing.dita" xtrc="li:3;23:21"><xref href="creating_a_docker_image_for_the_oxygen_publishing_engine.dita" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/server_side_building_and_publishing.dita" xtrc="xref:4;23:97" type="concept"><?ditaot gentext?>Creating a Docker Image for the Oxygen Publishing Engine</xref> and
                    then <xref href="running_the_publishing_engine_docker_image_on_aws.dita" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/server_side_building_and_publishing.dita" xtrc="xref:5;24:95" type="concept"><?ditaot gentext?>Running the Publishing Engine Docker Image on AWS</xref>.</li>
                <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/server_side_building_and_publishing.dita" xtrc="li:4;25:21"><xref href="https://www.oxygenxml.com/doc/ug-editor/topics/dcpp_running_pdf_from_integration_server.html" format="html" scope="external" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/server_side_building_and_publishing.dita" xtrc="xref:6;27:56"><?ditaot usertext?>Creating a Maven project and running it from
                        a Jenkins Job</xref>.</li>
            </ul></p>
        <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/server_side_building_and_publishing.dita" xtrc="p:3;30:12">Features of the <xref href="https://www.oxygenxml.com/publishing_engine.html" format="html" scope="external" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/server_side_building_and_publishing.dita" xtrc="xref:7;31:48"><?ditaot usertext?>Oxygen Publishing Engine</xref>:<dl id="dl_mlg_hhj_5zb" class="- topic/dl " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/server_side_building_and_publishing.dita" xtrc="dl:1;32:37">
                <dlentry class="- topic/dlentry " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/server_side_building_and_publishing.dita" xtrc="dlentry:1;33:26">
                    <dt class="- topic/dt " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/server_side_building_and_publishing.dita" xtrc="dt:1;34:25">Publishing WebHelp Responsive Output</dt>
                    <dd class="- topic/dd " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/server_side_building_and_publishing.dita" xtrc="dd:1;35:25">The <xref href="webhelp-dita-strong-points.dita" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/server_side_building_and_publishing.dita" xtrc="xref:8;36:68" type="topic"><?ditaot usertext?>WebHelp Responsive</xref> system features
                        a very flexible layout and is designed to adapt to any device and screen
                        size to provide an optimal viewing and interaction experience. It is based
                        upon the <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/server_side_building_and_publishing.dita" xtrc="i:1;39:37">Bootstrap</i> responsive front-end framework and is available
                        for DITA document types.</dd>
                </dlentry>
                <dlentry class="- topic/dlentry " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/server_side_building_and_publishing.dita" xtrc="dlentry:2;42:26">
                    <dt class="- topic/dt " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/server_side_building_and_publishing.dita" xtrc="dt:2;43:25">Publishing PDF based on CSS</dt>
                    <dd class="- topic/dd " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/server_side_building_and_publishing.dita" xtrc="dd:2;44:25">You can use the same Publishing Templates to build both the WebHelp and PDF
                        outputs. The <xref href="https://styles.oxygenxml.com/" format="html" scope="external" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/server_side_building_and_publishing.dita" xtrc="xref:9;46:46"><?ditaot usertext?>Oxygen Styles Basket</xref> allows you to build a base
                        publishing template visual customization based on CSS, and this
                        customization can later be used to produce the outputs.</dd>
                </dlentry>
                <dlentry class="- topic/dlentry " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/server_side_building_and_publishing.dita" xtrc="dlentry:3;50:26">
                    <dt class="- topic/dt " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/server_side_building_and_publishing.dita" xtrc="dt:3;51:25">Publishing to Zendesk</dt>
                    <dd class="- topic/dd " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/server_side_building_and_publishing.dita" xtrc="dd:3;52:25">The Enterprise edition of the license allows you to publish DITA XML content
                        directly as <b id="b_fr1_qtm_vzb" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/server_side_building_and_publishing.dita" xtrc="b:1;53:59">Zendesk</b> articles.</dd>
                </dlentry>
                <dlentry class="- topic/dlentry " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/server_side_building_and_publishing.dita" xtrc="dlentry:4;55:26">
                    <dt class="- topic/dt " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/server_side_building_and_publishing.dita" xtrc="dt:4;56:25">Change Tracking and Comments in the Published Output</dt>
                    <dd class="- topic/dd " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/server_side_building_and_publishing.dita" xtrc="dd:4;57:25">You can enable a parameter to show Oxygen tracked changes and comments in
                        the generated WebHelp and PDF outputs.</dd>
                </dlentry>
                <dlentry class="- topic/dlentry " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/server_side_building_and_publishing.dita" xtrc="dlentry:5;60:26">
                    <dt class="- topic/dt " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/server_side_building_and_publishing.dita" xtrc="dt:5;61:25">Syntax Highlight inside Code Blocks</dt>
                    <dd class="- topic/dd " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/server_side_building_and_publishing.dita" xtrc="dd:5;62:25"><xref href="https://www.oxygenxml.com/doc/ug-editor/topics/add-syntax-highlights-codeblocks.html" format="html" scope="external" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/server_side_building_and_publishing.dita" xtrc="xref:10;64:60"><?ditaot usertext?>Syntax highlights</xref> of code blocks
                        in the WebHelp and PDF outputs.</dd>
                </dlentry>
                <dlentry class="- topic/dlentry " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/server_side_building_and_publishing.dita" xtrc="dlentry:6;67:26">
                    <dt class="- topic/dt " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/server_side_building_and_publishing.dita" xtrc="dt:6;68:25">Embedding Media Video/Audio Resources</dt>
                    <dd class="- topic/dd " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/server_side_building_and_publishing.dita" xtrc="dd:6;69:25"><xref href="https://www.oxygenxml.com/doc/ug-editor/topics/whr-add-videos.html" format="html" scope="external" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/server_side_building_and_publishing.dita" xtrc="xref:11;71:60"><?ditaot usertext?>Embed video and audio resources</xref> in
                        the published WebHelp and PDF outputs.</dd>
                </dlentry>
                <dlentry class="- topic/dlentry " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/server_side_building_and_publishing.dita" xtrc="dlentry:7;74:26">
                    <dt class="- topic/dt " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/server_side_building_and_publishing.dita" xtrc="dt:7;75:25">DITA Metrics Report</dt>
                    <dd class="- topic/dd " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/server_side_building_and_publishing.dita" xtrc="dd:7;76:25">Build <xref href="https://www.oxygenxml.com/doc/ug-editor/topics/dita-map-metrics-report-2.html" format="html" scope="external" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/server_side_building_and_publishing.dita" xtrc="xref:12;78:60"><?ditaot usertext?>statistics and metrics</xref> for a DITA
                        XML project.</dd>
                </dlentry>
                <dlentry class="- topic/dlentry " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/server_side_building_and_publishing.dita" xtrc="dlentry:8;81:26">
                    <dt class="- topic/dt " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/server_side_building_and_publishing.dita" xtrc="dt:8;82:25">Dynamic Word/Excel/OpenAPI/Makdown to DITA Conversions</dt>
                    <dd class="- topic/dd " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/server_side_building_and_publishing.dita" xtrc="dd:8;83:25">Dynamically convert <xref href="https://www.oxygenxml.com/doc/ug-editor/topics/dynamically_convert_word_excel_html_markdown_to_dita.html" format="html" scope="external" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/server_side_building_and_publishing.dita" xtrc="xref:13;85:60"><?ditaot usertext?>Word/Excel/OpenAPI and Markdown
                            files</xref> referenced in the DITA Map to DITA XML content while
                        publishing.</dd>
                </dlentry>
                <dlentry class="- topic/dlentry " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/server_side_building_and_publishing.dita" xtrc="dlentry:9;89:26">
                    <dt class="- topic/dt " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/server_side_building_and_publishing.dita" xtrc="dt:9;90:25">Add Edit Links to Published Output</dt>
                    <dd class="- topic/dd " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/server_side_building_and_publishing.dita" xtrc="dd:9;91:25">Add <xref href="https://www.oxygenxml.com/doc/ug-editor/topics/wh-edit-link.html" format="html" scope="external" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="file:/D:/syncprojects/blog/topics/server_side_building_and_publishing.dita" xtrc="xref:14;93:60"><?ditaot usertext?>edit links</xref> for each published
                        topic, connecting the published output to an online editor for providing
                        feedback.</dd>
                </dlentry>
            </dl></p>
